24/06/2004
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Croatian Justice Minister Vesna Skare Ozbolt met with UN chief war crimes prosecutor Carla del Ponte on Wednesday (23 June). 
Afterwards, Skare Ozbolt said they had discussed co-operation between the Croatian government and the UN war crimes tribunal, and the transfer of war crimes cases to Croatian courts. 
They also discussed the recent OSCE report on the Croatian judiciary and its ability to handle war crimes cases, which Skare Ozbolt described as "quite positive".
In other news, the head of the OSCE mission to Croatia, Peter Semneby, visited Bjelovar-Bilogora County, a region ethnic Serbs fled during the 1990s conflict. 
Semneby met with the county prefect, Damir Bajs, and the head of the Croatian Association of Judges, Vladimir Gredelj.
Also Wednesday, Croatia completed the last section of a major highway linking Zagreb with Rijeka and the country's Adriatic resorts. 
The project is seen as a major boost for the travel industry. 
(HINA, HRT, AFP - 23/06/04)
